GENAI ENGINEER — 7 DAY COMPLETE LEARNING PLAN
DAY 1 — FOUNDATIONS & HOW LLMS REALLY WORK
Objective

Build a strong mental model of how Large Language Models work and remove the “black-box” mindset.

Topics Covered

Software & Python Foundations

Python essentials (functions, OOP, typing, async basics)

Virtual environments and dependency management

Git and repository structure

Logging, error handling, retries

Environment variables and configuration patterns

LLM Core Concepts

What a Language Model is

Tokens vs words

Context window and truncation

Training vs inference

Why hallucinations occur

Transformer architecture (attention, embeddings, positional encoding)

Decoding & Sampling

Temperature, top-p, top-k

Why randomness happens

Why repetition happens

Outcome

Able to explain transformers and hallucinations in simple terms

Interview-ready understanding of LLM behavior

DAY 2 — TOKENIZATION, EMBEDDINGS & SIMILARITY SEARCH
Objective

Understand how raw text becomes vectors and how semantic search works.

Topics Covered

Tokenization

BPE, WordPiece, SentencePiece

Token IDs and vocabulary

Token cost estimation

Prompt compression awareness

Embeddings

What embeddings represent

Cosine similarity vs dot product

Embedding dimensionality tradeoffs

Chunking fundamentals

Duplicate and noisy chunk issues

Outcome

Clear understanding of why chunking exists

Ability to explain why bad chunking breaks RAG systems

DAY 3 — PROMPT ENGINEERING (PRODUCTION LEVEL)
Objective

Control LLM outputs reliably and safely.

Topics Covered

Prompting Fundamentals

System vs user roles

Zero-shot vs few-shot prompting

Structured outputs (JSON, schemas)

Prompt templates and versioning

Advanced Prompting

Prompt debugging techniques

Hallucination control

Extraction vs reasoning prompts

Prompt injection awareness

Knowing when prompting is insufficient

Outcome

Ability to debug broken prompts

Confidence in designing production prompts

DAY 4 — LLM APIS, PROVIDERS & BACKEND ENGINEERING
Objective

Think like a backend GenAI engineer.

Topics Covered

LLM Providers

OpenAI, Azure OpenAI, Anthropic, Gemini

Model selection tradeoffs

Streaming vs non-streaming responses

Rate limits, retries, backoff strategies

Token usage tracking and cost control

Backend Engineering

FastAPI fundamentals

Async endpoints

Caching concepts

Secrets and authentication

Error handling patterns

Outcome

Ability to explain latency vs cost vs quality tradeoffs

Ready to build GenAI APIs

DAY 5 — RETRIEVAL AUGMENTED GENERATION (RAG)
Objective

Build real-world, grounded GenAI systems.

Topics Covered

RAG Fundamentals

Why RAG exists

RAG vs fine-tuning vs long-context models

Why fine-tuning does not add knowledge

Knowledge freshness and grounding

RAG Pipeline

Document ingestion (PDF, DOC, HTML)

Cleaning and normalization

Chunking strategies

Metadata design

Vector databases (FAISS, Pinecone, Chroma, etc.)

Retrieval strategies (top-k, MMR)

Reranking

Faithful answering with citations

Evaluation

Recall@k

Faithfulness vs relevance

Common failure modes

Outcome

Ability to design and defend a RAG architecture

Strong interview-level understanding of RAG systems

DAY 6 — AGENTS, LANGGRAPH & DOCUMENT AI
Objective

Move from chatbots to decision-making systems.

Topics Covered

AI Agents

What an AI agent is

Planning vs execution

Tool calling

Memory types

Failure recovery and fallbacks

Frameworks

LangChain fundamentals

LangGraph state machines

When not to use frameworks

Document AI (Invoice-Focused)

OCR and layout parsing

Table and key-value extraction

Rule-based + LLM hybrid validation

Confidence scoring

Human-in-the-loop workflows

Outcome

Clear understanding of agentic AI

Ability to explain responsible automation design

DAY 7 — PRODUCTION, SAFETY, MLOPS & INTERVIEW READINESS
Objective

Think like someone who ships GenAI systems.

Topics Covered

Safety & Governance

PII handling and redaction

Prompt injection defenses

Output filtering

Audit logs

Access control and data isolation

Enterprise compliance awareness (SOC2, GDPR)

Evaluation & Monitoring

Prompt regression testing

RAG quality evaluation

Latency and cost monitoring

Drift and failure alerts

Deployment & MLOps

Docker fundamentals

CI/CD awareness

Dev vs staging vs production environments

Self-hosted inference awareness (vLLM, Ollama)

System Design & Interviews

End-to-end GenAI architecture

Scaling strategies

Cost optimization

Human-in-the-loop placement

Outcome

Confident GenAI system design explanations

Strong readiness for GenAI Engineer interviews

FINAL RESULT

After completing this 7-day plan:

Full coverage of GenAI Engineer responsibilities

Production-ready mindset

Interview-ready explanations

Clear direction for building a flagship GenAI project
